## When implementing custom passkey UI

Use `ModuleFE_PasskeyAuth` directly instead of the built-in components:

```typescript
import {ModuleFE_PasskeyAuth} from '@nu-art/passkey-frontend';

// Check browser support:
if (!ModuleFE_PasskeyAuth.browserSupportsPasskeys()) { /* hide passkey UI */ }

// Login (unauthenticated):
await ModuleFE_PasskeyAuth.login();
// On success, the backend sets the JWT on the response — standard session flow.

// Register (requires session):
const result = await ModuleFE_PasskeyAuth.register('My Laptop');
// Returns { credential: { _id, credentialId, label, transports, backedUp } }

// Delete credential (requires session):
await ModuleFE_PasskeyAuth.deleteCredential({ credentialId: 'cred-id-here' });
```

After registration or deletion, refresh the credential list:
```typescript
import {ModuleFE_PasskeyCredentialDB} from '@nu-art/passkey-frontend';
await ModuleFE_PasskeyCredentialDB.query();
```

