## Forbidden patterns

- **Do not call `registerOptions` or `registerVerify` without an authenticated session** — the backend reads `MemKey_AccountId` to associate the credential with the account. Without a session this will fail.
- **Do not hardcode `rpId` with a protocol or port** — it must be the bare domain (`localhost`, `example.com`). The protocol and port go in `origin`.
- **Do not skip `loginOptions`/`loginVerify` in the open APIs list** — these endpoints must be accessible without a session. Omitting them from `openApis` will cause 401 errors for unauthenticated users trying to log in.
- **Do not reuse challenges** — challenges are single-use. After verification (success or failure), the challenge is deleted from the in-memory store.
- **Do not import from `@simplewebauthn/*` in consuming packages** — the passkey library wraps these. Consumers interact only with `ModuleFE_PasskeyAuth` / `ModuleBE_PasskeyAuth`.
- **Do not call `ModuleFE_PasskeyCredentialDB.v1.sync()`** — there is no `.v1` accessor. Use `ModuleFE_PasskeyCredentialDB.query()` to refresh the credential list.
